FBIS3-36362 "drsov024_d_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-024 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Feb 1994 Regional Affairs Terrorist Ultimatum on Yakutsk Expires LD0402110594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1026 GMT 4 Feb 94 LD0402110594 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] [Text] Moscow February 4 TASS -- The Siberian city of Yakutsk is heavily guarded on Friday as an ultimatum to explode its major infrastructure facilites received from an unknown terrorist group expires. A group called "Retribution", of which nobody had ever heard in Yakutsk, demanded to be paid 500,000 US dollars and 500 million rubles threatening to explode life-supporting facilities of the city. The Russian Interior Ministry told TASS that police in Yakutsk believe the threat is just a bluff; however, army experts joined police in a search for explosives. Special headquarters were created to monitor the situation and reinforced police units are patrolling the city. Everything was quiet in Yakutsk as for 18.00 hours local time, Mayor Aleksey Tomtosov told TASS by telephone adding that all important objects are heavily guarded.
